            <description><![CDATA[The S Pen still isn&#039;t utilized properly, though
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.androidpolice.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/04/DeX-Hero.png" class=" no-style"><img loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-hero-size wp-image-757104" src="https://www.androidpolice.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/04/DeX-Hero-728x410.png" alt="" width="728" height="410" srcset="https://www.androidpolice.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/04/DeX-Hero-728x410.png 728w, https://www.androidpolice.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/04/DeX-Hero-329x185.png 329w, https://www.androidpolice.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/04/DeX-Hero-668x376.png 668w, https://www.androidpolice.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/04/DeX-Hero-161x91.png 161w, https://www.androidpolice.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/04/DeX-Hero-217x122.png 217w, https://www.androidpolice.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/04/DeX-Hero.png 1920w" sizes="(max-width: 728px) 100vw, 728px"/></a></p>
<p>When Samsung announced that DeX would be going wireless in One UI 2.5, which was introduced on the Note20, I was excited. Until that point, I'd hardly touched the app because of the requirement to plug my phone into my PC. Sadly, wireless DeX only worked with compatible TVs and monitors, leaving most computers in the cold. Now with One UI 3.1 on the Galaxy S21, that's finally changed.<br />
<span id="more-757033"></span></p>
<p>The first thing you'll need to do to get started with wireless connectivity is to update to the latest version of the DeX client on your PC.</p><div class=clear></div> <a href="https://www.androidpolice.com/2021/02/04/samsung-dex-now-works-wirelessly-on-pcs-if-you-have-a-galaxy-s21/" class="read-more">Read More </a><p><a href='https://www.androidpolice.com/2021/02/04/samsung-dex-now-works-wirelessly-on-pcs-if-you-have-a-galaxy-s21/'>Samsung DeX now works wirelessly on PCs, if you have a Galaxy S21</a> was written by the awesome team at <a href='http://www.androidpolice.com'>Android Police</a>.</p>]]></description>

