<p>We've known about Google Chrome's quick page-sharing through dino-themed QR codes <a href="https://www.androidpolice.com/2019/12/06/chrome-working-on-qr-code-based-page-sharing-featuring-the-offline-dino/">since 2019</a>. After an <a href="https://www.androidpolice.com/2020/04/16/chrome-qr-code-sharing-feature-goes-live-in-canary-with-a-little-dino-help/">initial release in Canary</a> and more development, the feature first became available in Chrome 84. It's been working properly on both Android and desktops since then, but you had to manually enable the flag to get it going. With Chrome 88, QR codes are starting to roll out widely as part of a server-side change, as reported by <a href="https://www.smartdroid.de/qr-google-bringt-neue-taste-in-die-adressleiste-seines-browsers/">SmartDroid</a>.</p><div class=clear></div> <a href="https://www.androidpolice.com/2021/02/04/chrome-84-brings-new-dino-themed-qr-codes-to-android-and-desktops/" class="read-more">Read More </a><p><a href='https://www.androidpolice.com/2021/02/04/chrome-84-brings-new-dino-themed-qr-codes-to-android-and-desktops/'>Chrome 88 rolls out dino-themed QR codes on Android and desktop</a> was written by the awesome team at <a href='http://www.androidpolice.com'>Android Police</a>.</p>]]></description>

